# initial_program.py

import random

# EVOLVE-BLOCK-START
def run_search():
    n = 47
    # all grid points
    grid = [(x,y) for x in range(n) for y in range(n)]
    S = []
    random.shuffle(grid)
    for (x,y) in grid:
        ok = True
        # check collinearity against every point already in S
        for i in range(len(S)):
            x1, y1 = S[i]
            # collinear iff (y1-y)*(x1 - x) == 0 or (y1-y)*(x1 - x)
            if (y1 - y)*(x1 - x) == (y - y1)*(x - x1):
                ok = False
                break
        if ok:
            S.append((x,y))
    return S
# EVOLVE-BLOCK-END
